<?xml version="1.0"?>
<fed2-map title='Mars' version='39' editor='standard' from='772' to='Sol.Sol Space.722'>

   <location num='0' flags='t'>
      <name>Martian storeroom</name>
      <desc>   You think the Martians are gone, but really they are in hiding in this secret room!</desc>
   </location>

   <location num='79'>
      <name>Nuclear reactor</name>
      <desc>   You jump into the liquid, and dive below the surface...</desc>
      <exits up='143' out='143'/>
      <events in-room='death.ruins.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='140' flags='t'>
      <name>Pit</name>
      <desc>   You move along the ledge, very slowly and carefully...</desc>
      <exits se='205' up='205'/>
      <events in-room='death.ruins.2'/>
   </location>

   <location num='143' flags='t'>
      <name>Pit room</name>
      <desc>   This is a large room with strange artifacts built into its walls. In the middle is a pit filled with liquid, from which emanates an eerie blue glow.</desc>
      <desc>   Apart from going down into the pit, there are exits to the east and the south.</desc>
      <exits e='144' s='207' down='79' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='144' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   The floor of this east/west passage is completely smooth, with not a lump, bump or crack on it.</desc>
      <exits e='145' w='143' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='145' flags='t'>
      <name>Narrow passage</name>
      <desc>   You squeeze through a very restricted passage which runs from the west to the southeast.</desc>
      <exits se='210' w='144'/>
   </location>

   <location num='146' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   This is the west end of a passage. There is an exit to the south of your present position.</desc>
      <exits e='147' s='210' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='147' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   The passage is made from - or carved out of - or lined with - red sandstone, and it leads east and west.</desc>
      <exits e='148' w='146' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='148' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   The ceiling of this east/west passage is quite low. There seems to be a room to the south.</desc>
      <exits e='149' s='212' w='147' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='149' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   The passage turns through a right angle and runs off to the south and the west.</desc>
      <exits s='213' w='148' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='153' flags='t'>
      <name>Dummy location</name>
      <desc>   This dummy location provides the movement out of the treasure room. You shouldn&apos;t be here. If by any chance you are, type OUT to escape - and email feedback@ibgames.net to tell us about it!</desc>
      <exits out='408'/>
      <events enter='moves.ruins.2'/>
   </location>

   <location num='205' flags='t'>
      <name>Deep pit</name>
      <desc>   You are standing on a ledge which runs round the south and southeast sides of a deep pit. Looking down you can see the skeletons of previous explorers who fell to their deaths.</desc>
      <exits n='140' ne='140' e='140' se='270' s='269' sw='140' w='140' nw='140' up='140' down='140' in='140' out='140'/>
   </location>

   <location num='207' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   You are in a small passage running from the north to the southwest.</desc>
      <exits n='143' sw='270' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='208' flags='t'>
      <name>Dormitory</name>
      <desc>   You are in what was once a large dormitory area. Light seeps in through a gap in the ceiling, revealing a series of wide ledges that presumably served as beds for the Martians. A lost explorer must have lain down here to die in despair, leaving a pile of bones, the most recognizable of which are the ribs - judging from the size, he, she or it was a giant humanoid of some kind.</desc>
      <desc>   The room continues to the east and the south.</desc>
      <exits e='209' se='273' s='272' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='209' flags='t'>
      <name>Dormitory</name>
      <desc>   You are standing in the northeast corner of a large derelict dormitory. There are the remains of a door to the southeast.</desc>
      <exits se='274' s='273' sw='272' w='208' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='210' flags='t'>
      <name>Map room</name>
      <desc>   This very large room has one wall completely given over to a huge map of the whole complex.</desc>
      <desc>   Most of the map is still there, though bits have faded, but since you can&apos;t read Martian, you can&apos;t find the &apos;You Are Here&apos; sign. Consequently, the map is not much use to you.</desc>
      <desc>   There are exits to the north and northwest.</desc>
      <exits n='146' nw='145' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='211' flags='t'>
      <name>Shelf room</name>
      <desc>   All the walls of this room - except the northern one - are covered with empty shelves. On the north wall someone has daubed in red paint (or perhaps it&apos;s blood?) &apos;Jim Morrison Lives!&apos;.</desc>
      <desc>   The room continues to the south, and there is an exit to the southwest.</desc>
      <exits s='275' sw='274' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='212' flags='t'>
      <name>Machine room</name>
      <desc>   The room is filled with the remains of old Martian machines, their use long since forgotten. Anything moveable was stolen or salvaged long ago.</desc>
      <desc>   There is an exit to the north, and a hole in the wall to the southwest.</desc>
      <exits n='148' sw='275' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='213' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   The passage divides at this point. Branches run off to the north, the south, and the southwest.</desc>
      <exits n='149' s='277' sw='276' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='216' flags='t'>
      <name>Treasure room</name>
      <desc>   The walls of this room appear to be made of pure gold! Unfortunately, there is no way that you can get a purchase to strip the metal off the wall.</desc>
      <desc>   In the middle of the room is a black marble block topped by a white pedestal. The top of the pedestal is chalice-shaped. The room continues to the east.</desc>
      <exits e='217'/>
   </location>

   <location num='217' flags='t'>
      <name>Treasure room</name>
      <desc>   This room reminds you of the room that teleported you here. The walls are made from the same black opaline material, and have the same slick feel to them.</desc>
      <exits n='153' ne='153' e='153' se='153' s='153' sw='153' w='216' nw='153' up='153' down='153' in='153' out='153'/>
   </location>

   <location num='259' flags='bt'>
      <name>Roof garden</name>
      <desc>   Unlike the bar, the Christmas decorations on the roof display a modicum of taste, and it looks like a snowy winter garden. The huge exotic plants which hide the ducts and pipework have been sprayed with something so they look as if they are covered with glistening ice. Tiny white lights glimmer amongst the leaves, twinkling on and off, and artificial icicles hang from the branches.</desc>
      <desc>   Some kind of fake snow covers the floor; it crunches when you walk on it. It has drifted around the edges of the roof, merging with the forcefield that stops those imbued with the Christmas spirit from tumbling off the edge. Two off-duty waitdroids are scraping up handfulls of the artificial snow and hurling snowballs at each other. There&apos;s plenty of snow to go around so if you want to join in the fun, GET SNOWBALL.</desc>
      <desc>   An open trapdoor reveals the top of a spiral staircase leading down into the bar, from where you can hear the soft notes of Phil&apos;s piano, reluctantly playing Christmas songs.</desc>
      <exits down='260' in='260'/>
      <events in-room='xmas09.snowball.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='260' flags='bt'>
      <name>Chez Diesel</name>
      <desc>   Diesel has decorated her famous bar for the festive season, and has eschewed good taste and gone for the kitsch Christmas look. The walls are covered with brightly colored fairy lights, which flash on and off gaudily. Paper chains and foil decorations hang from every bit of the ceiling. A large inflatable snowman sits in one corner, rocking backwards and forwards and giggling manically. It&apos;s actually quite scary!</desc>
      <desc>   Phil, the ancient Arcturian piano player, is reluctantly playing a selection of ancient traditional Christmas songs, but from the way he is scowling - and the sign on the piano that says &quot;No I won&apos;t play bloody Jingle Bells!&quot; - he isn&apos;t exactly full of the joys of Christmas.</desc>
      <desc>   The waitdroids all have tinsel and colored flashing lights wrapped around them. It&apos;s a wonder they can see to serve the customers the free food and drink.</desc>
      <desc>   The banister of the stairs leading to the roof is festooned with those thin strips of silver paper that are meant to look like icicles.</desc>
      <exits se='325' up='259' down='325' out='325' no-exit='moves.noexit.2'/>
      <events enter='party.fireworks.11' in-room='newbod.card.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='261'>
      <name>City street</name>
      <desc>   This is the northern end of a long road. To the east is a shop.</desc>
      <exits e='262' s='325' in='262'/>
   </location>

   <location num='262' flags='a'>
      <name>Magdalena and Daughters Trading Post</name>
      <desc>   When Mars was first settled, this store sold the essentials of daily life - from food to vital equipment that kept the colonists alive. Magdalena and her family made a fortune from this captive market, but she reinvested her profits back into the store rather than spending it on herself.</desc>
      <desc>   This part of the store still sells those essentials, but a much greater range, including items imported from Earth and the other planets.</desc>
      <desc>   The store currently has a special offer on cheese from Earth. A small slice will cost you 10 groats.</desc>
      <desc>   The shop extends to the south.</desc>
      <exits s='326' w='261' in='326' out='261'/>
   </location>

   <location num='269' flags='t'>
      <name>Pillared room</name>
      <desc>   You are in a large room with a huge vaulted ceiling. The ceiling is supported by rows of pillars which march down the middle of the room. There are exits to the north and the southwest.</desc>
      <exits n='205' sw='332' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='270' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   This is a small passage running from the northwest to the northeast.</desc>
      <exits ne='207' nw='205' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='271' flags='t'>
      <name>Altar</name>
      <desc>   The church&apos;s main altar is a stunning sight. It is a large, triangular slab fashioned from something the color of gold, but it must be a much tougher metal because it has survived for all these centuries without a scratch. In the center of the altar is a hole into which members of the congregation would drop their offerings in order to appease the Martian gods, and receive a blessing from the priests.</desc>
      <desc>   Hanging above the altar is the biggest holo you have ever seen, depicting a white, square room whose walls have been disfigured by some red stains.</desc>
      <desc>   There is an opening in the front of the altar, from which stairs lead down into darkness.</desc>
      <exits se='336' s='335' sw='334' down='524' in='524' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='272' flags='t'>
      <name>Dormitory</name>
      <desc>   This is the southwestern corner of a large, half-wrecked dormitory area.</desc>
      <exits n='208' ne='209' e='273' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='273' flags='t'>
      <name>Dormitory</name>
      <desc>   You are standing in the southeast corner of a large dormitory area. Light seeps in through cracks and gaps in the roof. There is an exit to the southeast.</desc>
      <exits n='209' se='338' w='272' nw='208' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='274' flags='t'>
      <name>Antechamber</name>
      <desc>   It is impossible to guess the original function of this small, bare antechamber. There are exits to the northeast and the northwest.</desc>
      <exits ne='211' nw='209' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='275' flags='t'>
      <name>Shelf room</name>
      <desc>   Most of the space in this room is taken up by shelving. The contents of the shelves have long since been looted. The room continues to the north, and there is a hole in the northeast wall.</desc>
      <exits n='211' ne='212' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='276' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   The southwest end of this passage runs into an open space, while to the northeast the passage continues.</desc>
      <exits ne='213' sw='339' in='213' out='339' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='277' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   You are in a north/south passage with nothing remarkable about it.</desc>
      <exits n='213' s='341' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='322' flags='ba'>
      <name>Hotel lounge</name>
      <desc>   This is a very smart lounge, as you would expect from such a high-class hotel. You don&apos;t really fit in, but the staff are professional enough to ignore that, and serve you anyway. After all, rich eccentrics are sometimes known to dress like tramp haulers!</desc>
      <desc>   A waitress - real human, not a droid - recommends the afternoon tea, which is served all day.</desc>
      <desc>   The exit to the hotel lobby is south.</desc>
      <exits s='386' out='386'/>
   </location>

   <location num='324' flags='a'>
      <name>Tux Deluxe</name>
      <desc>   This high-class establishment used to cater to the upper classes, providing them with the finest quality clothing for the best of occasions. However, new technology has rendered bespoke tailoring services obsolete, so the shop is attempting to sell off its stock at bargain prices before closing down.</desc>
      <desc>   Mannequins display the clothes that are for sale, festooned with large flashy signs declaring &quot;50% off&quot;, &quot;bargain prices&quot;, &quot;clothing slashed&quot; and &quot;everything must go&quot;.</desc>
      <desc>   The robotailor in the corner is starting to gather dust from disuse. It is now being used as a hatstand. At the moment it is displaying a selection of rather elegant gentlemens opera hats, priced at 10 groats each.</desc>
      <desc>   The exit is east.</desc>
      <exits e='325' out='325'/>
   </location>

   <location num='325'>
      <name>City street</name>
      <desc>   You are in a wide street running north/south. To the west is the entrance to a shop. A large sign in the shop window announces a closing down sale.</desc>
      <desc>   To the northwest a set of iron stairs run up to a discreet door on the second story of an otherwise undistinguished building, leading to the famous bar Chez Diesel. A sign affixed to the stairs indicates that the hopper Diesel has laid on to transport customers back to their ships has been replaced by a toboggan. Wait a short while and your transportation will arrive, then get IN.</desc>
      <exits n='261' s='389' w='324' nw='260' up='260'/>
      <events enter='party.poppers.3'/>
   </location>

   <location num='326' flags='a'>
      <name>Trading Post</name>
      <desc>   This southern part of the store has displays of more frivolous items, for entertainment and comfort, not just for staying alive. The stock varies depending on what ships from other worlds have brought. Right now, there are a number of slightly racy holos from an organization on Venus called Dirty Boy Productions.</desc>
      <desc>   There is also a display of Martian handicrafts - items made by the locals, such as statuettes and sculptures carved from chunks of red rock. Grotesquely caricatured images of the long-vanished Martians seem particularly popular.</desc>
      <exits n='262' out='262'/>
   </location>

   <location num='328'>
      <name>Empty shop</name>
      <desc>   The shop has been empty for some time, and all that is left is debris - anything of value has long since been taken away. You can hear a skittering, scampering noise, which suggests that marsrats have been making the building their home - the smell seems to confirm that.</desc>
      <desc>   The exit is southwest.</desc>
      <exits sw='391' out='391' no-exit='moves.noexit.6'/>
      <events in-room='objects.cheese.9'/>
   </location>

   <location num='332' flags='t'>
      <name>Blue room</name>
      <desc>   The room you have entered has walls which appear to be made of glowing blue sapphire! Nothing you do has the slightest effect on the substance - you can&apos;t chip it or scratch it.</desc>
      <desc>   The exits are to the northeast and the southeast.</desc>
      <exits ne='269' se='397' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='333' flags='t'>
      <name>Temple</name>
      <desc>   You are at the west end of a large temple.</desc>
      <exits e='334' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='334' flags='t'>
      <name>Temple</name>
      <desc>   You are in a gigantic temple. The temple continues to the east and the west. The altar is to the northeast.</desc>
      <exits ne='271' e='335' w='333' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='335' flags='t'>
      <name>Temple</name>
      <desc>   You are in the middle of a large temple. The altar is to the north, and the body of the temple continues to the east and the west.</desc>
      <exits n='271' e='336' w='334' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='336' flags='t'>
      <name>Temple</name>
      <desc>   You are in a large temple. To the northwest is the altar, and the main part of the temple continues to the east and the west.</desc>
      <exits e='337' w='335' nw='271' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='337' flags='t'>
      <name>Temple</name>
      <desc>   You are at the east end of a massive temple. There is an exit to your southeast.</desc>
      <exits se='402' w='336' out='402' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='338' flags='t'>
      <name>Guardroom</name>
      <desc>   You guess from the layout of this smallish room that it was probably a guardroom. There are exits to the east and the northwest.</desc>
      <exits e='339' nw='273' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='339' flags='t'>
      <name>Open space</name>
      <desc>   The ruins draw back, leaving an open space which continues to the south and the southeast, while to the west is the entrance to a large building. Northeast is another, rather uninviting opening.</desc>
      <exits ne='276' se='404' s='403' w='338' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='340' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   You are at the west end of a passage. To the south is an opening through which Mars&apos; pale sunlight filters.</desc>
      <exits e='341' s='404' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='341' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   The passage bends through a right angle at this point and runs off to the north and west.</desc>
      <exits n='277' w='340' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='348' flags='t'>
      <name>Dummy loc</name>
      <desc>This dummy location provides the movement out of the pentagonal room. You shouldn&apos;t be here. If by any chance you are, type OUT to escape - and email feedback@ibgames.net to tell us about it!</desc>
      <exits out='408'/>
      <events enter='moves.ruins.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='386' flags='a'>
      <name>Mars Interplanetary Hotel</name>
      <desc>   This is Mars&apos; only hotel, but despite the lack of competition, it&apos;s a very classy joint, and it charges accordingly. Only the super-stellar-rich can afford to stay here, so there&apos;s no chance of you affording a room.</desc>
      <desc>   The walls are covered with real wood paneling, and an impressive crystal chandelier hangs from the high ceiling.</desc>
      <desc>   The exit is east, and the hotel&apos;s lounge is north.</desc>
      <exits n='322' e='387' out='387'/>
   </location>

   <location num='387'>
      <name>City street</name>
      <desc>   This is the west end of an east/west road. The entrance to &apos;The Duff Modem&apos; pub is to the south. West is a large door, made of real terrestrial mahogany - the entrance to a hotel.</desc>
      <exits e='388' s='451' w='386' in='451'/>
   </location>

   <location num='388'>
      <name>City street</name>
      <desc>   The east/west street goes past unremarkable buildings.</desc>
      <exits e='389' w='387'/>
   </location>

   <location num='389'>
      <name>Crossroads</name>
      <desc>   The city&apos;s main crossroads has become a gathering place for the locals. From here streets go out to the four points of the compass, but everyone stops on their way, to pass the time of day with each other. To that end, benches have been placed on all four corners.</desc>
      <exits n='325' e='390' s='453' w='388'/>
      <events in-room='objects.marsrat.9'/>
   </location>

   <location num='390'>
      <name>City street</name>
      <desc>   This spacious road runs west, to a crossroads, and east, to the industrial part of the city. To the south is a building, from which come the sounds you associate with engineering.</desc>
      <exits e='391' s='454' w='389' in='454'/>
   </location>

   <location num='391'>
      <name>City street</name>
      <desc>   The street curves from the west to the southeast. To the northeast is a derelict building, that looks like it used to be a shop of some kind.</desc>
      <exits ne='328' se='456' w='390' in='328'/>
   </location>

   <location num='397' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   You are at the west end of a passageway. There is an exit to the northwest.</desc>
      <exits e='398' nw='332' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='398' flags='t'>
      <name>Passage</name>
      <desc>   The passageway stretches to the east and west, and the floor is relatively rubble-free.</desc>
      <exits e='399' w='397' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='399' flags='t'>
      <name>Rubble</name>
      <desc>   This east/west passage is choked with rubble, so much so that it is almost impassable. To the west the passage continues and becomes clearer, while to the east the passage is completely blocked by a bad cave-in.</desc>
      <exits e='400' w='398' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='400' flags='t'>
      <name>Narrow slit</name>
      <desc>   You force yourself through a narrow slit at the top of a dangerous pile of rubble. With great relief you reach the far side. Suddenly you are sliding down a pile of loose scree.</desc>
      <desc>   Ending up in a bruised heap at the bottom you look around. The passage continues to the west, but with all the loose scree there is no way you can get back.</desc>
      <desc>   Scrabbling upright again you disturb some of the scree and realize it conceals the shattered bones of lost explorers, who failed to find a way back out of the ruins again. Some of the bones are almost intact.</desc>
      <exits w='399' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='401' flags='t'>
      <name>Cave-in</name>
      <desc>   There has been a very bad cave-in in this area. To the southeast is a passageway.</desc>
      <desc>   At first sight the west end of the room appears to be completely blocked. However, careful examination reveals a small slit at the top. You could probably get through the slit, but you might wish you hadn&apos;t!</desc>
      <exits se='466' w='400' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='402' flags='t'>
      <name>Archway</name>
      <desc>   This is a small but sturdy archway which forms the entrance to a large building. East takes you out into the open, while northwest takes you farther into the building.</desc>
      <exits e='403' nw='337' in='337' out='403' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='403' flags='t'>
      <name>Open space</name>
      <desc>   You are standing in the southwest corner of a large open space. To your west is an archway, and south is a heap of rubble.</desc>
      <exits n='339' e='404' s='467' w='402' in='402' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='404' flags='t'>
      <name>Open space</name>
      <desc>   You are standing in an open space which continues west and northwest. North is a dark opening, and to your east is a curious five-sided building. To the south lie mounds of rubble.</desc>
      <exits n='340' e='405' s='468' w='403' nw='339' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='405' flags='t'>
      <name>Pentagonal room</name>
      <desc>   You are in a strange five-sided room which seethes with latent power. Shivers crawl up and down your spine from the power leakage.</desc>
      <desc>   The walls are made of a strange black opaline material with flecks of light in it. You have the feeling that s-o-m-e-t-h-i-n-g nasty is about to happen!</desc>
      <exits n='348' ne='348' e='348' se='348' s='348' sw='348' w='404' nw='348' up='348' down='348' in='348' out='348'/>
   </location>

   <location num='408' flags='t'>
