   <location num='451' flags='ba'>
      <name>The Duff Modem</name>
      <desc>   The public bar of this run-down, seedy establishment is in need of a makeover; the walls are brown with tobacco stains, the floor sticky with spilt beer and other, less savory fluids. But the customers seem to like it just as it is.</desc>
      <desc>   A sign over the bar hangs slightly aslant: &apos;Try Our Modem of Real Ale&apos;.</desc>
      <desc>   There is a door in the north wall.</desc>
      <exits n='387' out='387'/>
   </location>

   <location num='452' flags='e'>
      <name>Market</name>
      <desc>   The Mars trading exchange follows the standard design for such facilities, with indicator boards flashing up prices in a constant stream. Small knots of people cluster around them, some looking jubilant and others worried.</desc>
      <desc>   The exit is east.</desc>
      <exits e='453' out='453'/>
   </location>

   <location num='453'>
      <name>City street</name>
      <desc>   This is one of the city&apos;s main streets, running north/south through the heart of the most populated area. The planet&apos;s trading exchange is to the west.</desc>
      <exits n='389' s='517' w='452' in='452'/>
   </location>

   <location num='454' flags='a'>
      <name>Workshop</name>
      <desc>   The workshop is a jumble of equipment, some of which you recognize as the usual engineering paraphernalia - lathes, jigs, borers, etc - but other items are a complete mystery to you.</desc>
      <desc>   Skilled craftspeople are bent over workbenches, doing mysterious things. You wonder why they don&apos;t get droids to do it; surely it would be faster and cheaper?</desc>
      <desc>   The exit is north.</desc>
      <exits n='390' out='390'/>
   </location>

   <location num='456'>
      <name>Street</name>
      <desc>   This is the industrial part of Mars city, and the street is lined with warehouses. It runs from the northwest to the southeast. To the east is the entrance to a tall windowless building.</desc>
      <exits e='457' se='521' nw='391' in='457'/>
   </location>

   <location num='457'>
      <name>Large warehouse</name>
      <desc>   This enormous warehouse is stuffed full of boxes and crates, all of which are labelled, but using some kind of code which makes it impossible for you to tell what they contain. No doubt the staff here know how to find the things they need!</desc>
      <desc>   The warehouse continues east, and there is a large door in the west wall.</desc>
      <exits e='458' w='456' in='458' out='456'/>
   </location>

   <location num='458'>
      <name>Large warehouse</name>
      <desc>   This part of the warehouse contains small boxes, which it would be possible to lift and carry away - if it weren&apos;t for the fact that everything is protected by forcefields.</desc>
      <desc>   The warehouse continues to the west, and there is a door leading to an office in the east wall.</desc>
      <exits e='459' w='457' in='459' out='457'/>
   </location>

   <location num='459' flags='a'>
      <name>Office</name>
      <desc>   This is the office where all the records relating to the warehouse are kept. Actually, the only thing it contains is a data terminal - clearly everything is stored electronically, doing away with physical paperwork and forms to be filled in.</desc>
      <desc>   There is a door in the west wall, leading into the warehouse.</desc>
      <exits w='458' out='458'/>
   </location>

   <location num='466' flags='t'>
      <name>Rubble</name>
      <desc>   The narrow passage takes some negotiating, because the floor is covered with loose rubble. The rubble is worse to the northwest, but clearer to the south.</desc>
      <exits s='530' nw='401' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='467' flags='t'>
      <name>Rubble</name>
      <desc>   You are clambering over a heap of rubble from derelict buildings. The rubble continues to the east, while to the north is open space.</desc>
      <exits n='403' e='468' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='468' flags='t'>
      <name>Rubble</name>
