      <desc>   A busy north/south road leads from the city through to the spaceport.</desc>
      <exits n='517' s='645'/>
   </location>

   <location num='582'>
      <name>Beaten track</name>
      <desc>This small winding track runs through the outskirts of the city. To the northwest the track joins the main road, while to the southeast it vanishes into the distance.</desc>
      <exits se='647' nw='517'/>
   </location>

   <location num='584'>
      <name>Beaten track</name>
      <desc>   The track winds its way around a series of grim, windowless warehouses. One end of the track goes southeast, the other end southwest.</desc>
      <exits se='649' sw='647'/>
   </location>

   <location num='585' flags='a'>
      <name>Small warehouse</name>
      <desc>   This warehouse looks at first glance to be empty, although there are footprints in the thick layer of dust on the floor.</desc>
      <desc>   There is a door in the north wall.</desc>
      <exits n='521' out='521'/>
   </location>

   <location num='591' flags='t'>
      <name>Narrow slit</name>
      <desc>   This narrow, rubble-strewn space separates two tall buildings. It continues to the southwest, but to the north it opens out into a courtyard.</desc>
      <exits n='527' sw='654' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='592' flags='t'>
      <name>Archeologists&apos; storeroom</name>
      <desc>   There is nothing remarkable about this building, so over the years the archeologists investigating the ruins have used it to store their belongings in between workshifts. In the corner is a large box which contains a set of archeologists tools - you can see a trowel, a set of brushes, a pair of tweezers and a measuring tape.</desc>
      <desc>   A discarded sleeping bag on the floor shows that sometimes the archeologists stay the night in here - obviously, they are unaffected by the spookiness of the ruins!</desc>
      <desc>   The exit is southeast.</desc>
      <exits se='657' out='657' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='594' flags='t'>
      <name>Alleyway</name>
      <desc>   The serpentine little alleyway snakes its way from the east to the south. There is a hole in the wall to the north of your present position.</desc>
