   <location num='708' flags='a'>
      <name>Spaceport repairs</name>
      <desc>   The repair shop is a hive of activity - machines, humans and aliens all labor to make repairs to spacecraft of all shapes and sizes. If your ship needs repairs, you can get them done here...</desc>
      <desc>   The only visible exit is east, into the main terminal.</desc>
      <exits e='709' out='709'/>
   </location>

   <location num='709'>
      <name>Spaceport terminus</name>
      <desc>   You are in the main terminal of Marsport. To the west lie the repair sheds, south is the spaceport, and north is the main exit.</desc>
      <exits n='645' s='773' w='708' out='645'/>
   </location>

   <location num='711' flags='ta'>
      <name>Temple of Gaelaan</name>
      <desc>   From the outside, the hut looks like the kind of crude shelter erected by archeologists working on examining the nearby ruins. But once inside you realize that the circular space is much bigger than you expected - it appears to have been dug into the rock of a hillside.</desc>
      <desc>   The cult has not been operating for very long on Mars, so this temple is not as lavishly decorated as the one on Earth, about which you have seen holo documentaries. The room is dominated by a block of shimmering silver material - the altar.</desc>
      <desc>   Behind the altar you can see a heap of machinery, which looks like it has been taken from the ruins.</desc>
      <exits n='647'/>
   </location>

   <location num='714'>
      <name>Beaten track</name>
      <desc>   The path runs through open countryside, curving gently from the north to the southeast.</desc>
      <exits n='650' se='779'/>
   </location>

   <location num='719' flags='t'>
      <name>Narrow slit</name>
      <desc>   This narrow slit lets you squeeze between two buildings. It feels very claustrophobic... The slit continues to the northwest, but opens out to the east.</desc>
      <exits e='720' nw='654' out='720' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='720' flags='t'>
      <name>Alleyway</name>
      <desc>   The tiny alleyway runs from the northeast into a more open area in the south. There is an opening in the ruins to the west.</desc>
      <exits ne='657' s='784' w='719' in='719' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='721' flags='t'>
      <name>Long room</name>
      <desc>   This long curving room is lit through ragged gaps in its ceiling. The exit is through a gap in the northeast wall, and the room continues to the south.</desc>
      <exits ne='658' s='785' out='658' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='722' flags='t'>
      <name>Hazy Mist</name>
      <desc>   This room is full of a hazy mist. It doesn&apos;t feel damp, and it glows with an indeterminate light source. The mist is brighter to the north and darker to the south.</desc>
      <exits n='658' s='786' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='723' flags='t'>
      <name>Bare room</name>
      <desc>   This is a bare octagonal room with exits to the northeast and the east.</desc>
      <exits ne='660' e='724' out='660' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='724' flags='t'>
      <name>Empty room</name>
